                            <comment id="17936349" author="maedhroz" created="Tue, 18 Mar 2025 02:59:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This almost certainly applies to 5.0, but need to check 4.1 and 4.0 as well...&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17936350" author="maedhroz" created="Tue, 18 Mar 2025 03:01:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The proximate cause of the problem is that &lt;tt&gt;BTreeRow#hasComplexDeletion()&lt;/tt&gt; uses &lt;tt&gt;accumulate()&lt;/tt&gt;, which can overwrite an intermediate result indicating a complex deletion exists. It may go back to &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-15389&quot; title=&quot;Minimize BTree iterator allocations&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-15389&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-15389&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17936354" author="maedhroz" created="Tue, 18 Mar 2025 03:33:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;4.1 and 4.0 are safe.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17936356" author="maedhroz" created="Tue, 18 Mar 2025 03:36:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=adelapena&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;adelapena&quot;&gt;adelapena&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=bereng&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;bereng&quot;&gt;bereng&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=aratnofsky&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;aratnofsky&quot;&gt;aratnofsky&lt;/a&gt; It looks like this traces back to &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-14227&quot; title=&quot;Extend maximum expiration date&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-14227&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-14227&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. That patch changes the accumulator value in &lt;tt&gt;BTreeRow#hasComplexDeletion()&lt;/tt&gt; to &lt;tt&gt;Cell.MAX_DELETION_TIME&lt;/tt&gt;, but the value we use in &lt;tt&gt;BTree.isStopSentinel()&lt;/tt&gt; is still &lt;tt&gt;Long.MAX_VALUE&lt;/tt&gt;. Any reason not to just change it back?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
