                            <comment id="17936380" author="bereng" created="Tue, 18 Mar 2025 06:20:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Dropped a comment. Let&apos;s see what CI has to say about it?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17936532" author="maedhroz" created="Tue, 18 Mar 2025 15:02:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Initial 5.0 CI run looks fine, modulo my env having a Python dtest CCM issue and &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-20450&quot; title=&quot;Fix simulator dtests after CASSANDRA-20368&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-20450&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-20450&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17936646" author="dcapwell" created="Tue, 18 Mar 2025 23:28:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I updated org.apache.cassandra.distributed.test.cql3.MultiNodeTableWalkWithoutReadRepairTest to support collections, += and -= on collections as well, with this I was able to reproduce the issue and confirmed this patch fixes it&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17936872" author="maedhroz" created="Wed, 19 Mar 2025 15:40:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Looks like nothing but known flakes and a couple of env-related timeouts in CI...going to move ahead w/ commit...&lt;/p&gt;

